The man charged with the murder of 28-year-old Tshegofatso Pule appeared in the Roodepoort Magistrate's Court this morning - his case has been postponed until next month. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The man charged with the murder of 28-year-old Tshegofatso Pule appeared in the Roodepoort magistrate's court on Wednesday. The matter has been postponed until July. Mzikayise Malepane (31) appeared on camera from a correctional facility. READ: Tshegofatso Pule's alleged killer abandons bail bid It is alleged he was offered R70,000 in payment for Pule's murder. Pule's body was found in a veld in Durban Deep, Roodepoort earlier this month. Her death is one of several murders of women in the country recently and has lead to calls for the government to do more about South Africa's femicide crisis.